## 2. Technology Stack Deep Dive

### Frontend Technologies

| Technology | Purpose | Why Chosen |
|-----------|---------|------------|
| **React 18** | UI Framework | Component-based, virtual DOM, large ecosystem |
| **TypeScript** | Type Safety | Compile-time errors, better IntelliSense, maintainability |
| **Vite** | Build Tool | Fast HMR, ESM-native, smaller bundles than Webpack |
| **TailwindCSS** | Styling | Utility-first, no context switching, smaller CSS bundle |
| **shadcn/ui** | Components | Accessible, customizable, copy-paste components |
| **React Query** | Server State | Caching, background refetch, optimistic updates |

### Backend Services

| Service | Purpose | Why Chosen |
|---------|---------|------------|
| **Firebase RTDB** | Real-time data | Low latency, perfect for IoT, free tier |
| **Firebase Auth** | Authentication | Easy email/password, security rules integration |
| **Firebase FCM** | Push Notifications | Cross-platform, background support |
| **Ollama** | Local LLM | Privacy, no API costs, offline capable |

### Hardware

| Component | Purpose | Why Chosen |
|-----------|---------|------------|
| **ESP32** | Microcontroller | WiFi built-in, dual-core, 240MHz, cheap |
| **PIR Sensor** | Motion Detection | Low power, 120° angle, 7m range |
| **Flame Sensor** | Fire Detection | Infrared detection, fast response |
| **Ultrasonic** | Water Level | Non-contact, accurate distance measurement |
| **4-Channel Relay** | Device Control | Isolated switching, 10A per channel |

### Advantages & Disadvantages

#### React + TypeScript
**Advantages:**
- Strong type checking prevents runtime errors
- Better IDE support with autocomplete
- Easier refactoring
- Self-documenting code

**Disadvantages:**
- Learning curve for TypeScript
- More verbose code
- Build time slightly longer

#### Firebase Realtime Database
**Advantages:**
- Real-time sync across all clients
- Offline persistence
- Simple API
- Free tier sufficient for prototypes

**Disadvantages:**
- NoSQL structure can be limiting
- No native joins
- Pricing can scale with reads/writes

#### Ollama vs Cloud AI
**Advantages:**
- No API costs
- Data privacy - nothing leaves local network
- Works offline
- No rate limits

**Disadvantages:**
- Requires local compute resources
- Model quality may be lower than GPT-4
- Needs manual model management

