## 7. AI Chatbot System

### Architecture Overview

```mermaid
graph LR
    USER[User Input] --> CHATBOT[chatbot.tsx]
    CHATBOT --> CMD{Command<br>Detection}
    CMD -->|Device Command| FIREBASE[Firebase RTDB]
    CMD -->|Query| OLLAMA[Ollama LLM]
    OLLAMA --> PROXY[Python Proxy]
    PROXY --> OLLAMA_SERVER[Ollama Server]
    OLLAMA_SERVER --> PROXY
    PROXY --> CHATBOT
    CHATBOT --> RESPONSE[Response to User]
```

### Command Handler System

**File**: [src/chatbot.tsx](file:///e:/PROJECTS/clg%20project/IOT%20NEW/src/chatbot.tsx)

```typescript
async function handleCommand(userMessage) {
    const msg = userMessage.toLowerCase().trim();

    // ===== TIMER COMMANDS =====
    if (msg.includes("timer") && (msg.includes("status") || msg.includes("active"))) {
        return await getActiveTimersStatus();
    }

    if (msg.includes("cancel") && msg.includes("timer")) {
        const relay = findRelayFromText(msg);
        if (relay) {
            return await cancelRelayTimerFromChat(relay);
        }
        return "Please specify which device timer to cancel.";
    }

    // Check for timer command: "turn on/off X for Y time"
    const hasTimerKeyword = msg.includes("for ") || msg.includes("after ");
    if (hasTimerKeyword) {
        const duration = parseTimerDuration(msg);
        if (duration.totalSeconds > 0) {
            const relay = findRelayFromText(msg);
            if (relay) {
                const isTurningOn = msg.includes("on") || msg.includes("chalu");
                
                if (isTurningOn) {
                    // Turn on immediately, set timer to turn OFF
                    await set(ref(database, `relays/${relay}`), false);
                    await setRelayTimerFromChat(relay, duration.hours, duration.minutes, duration.seconds, 'off');
                    return `✅ ${RELAY_NAMES[relay]} turned ON! Will turn OFF in ${formatDurationText(duration.totalSeconds)}. ⏰`;
                }
            }
        }
    }

    // ... more command handling

    // No command matched, return null to let Ollama handle
    return null;
}
```

**Command priority:**
1. Timer status queries
2. Cancel timer commands
3. Timer set commands
4. Device on/off commands
5. Sensor status queries
6. Fall through to AI

